codex
The new decision-rule module hard-codes extra point-estimate comparisons into both probe gates, which makes the executable preregistration stricter than the documented CI-based rule. Those false negatives can change downstream slice decisions even when the paired statistics satisfy the frozen criteria.

Full review comments:

- [P2] Drop raw-point comparison from the 15a pass gate — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/python/eval/decision_rule_083.py:232-233
  `probe_15a_pass` is supposed to implement the preregistered rule "margin CI lower bound > 0" on both metrics, but these lines add an extra `cand > base` point-estimate check. That changes the rule for any caller that passes rounded summary points: a candidate can legitimately have `eu8_margin_ci_lo > 0` / `hard_margin_ci_lo > 0` and still tie after rounding, which will now be reported as FAIL and incorrectly suppress the embedder promotion decision for Slice 20.

- [P2] Base the 15b placebo gate on the paired margin only — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/python/eval/decision_rule_083.py:260-260
  The preregistration for 15b says the proxy passes when the paired `enriched - placebo` CI lower bound is `> 0` and the length-norm penalty is removed. Requiring `enriched["recall"] > placebo["recall"]` adds a second, unregistered gate, so a rounded/exported summary can fail here even when the paired analysis already proves a positive margin. That would incorrectly defer or drop Slice 25 despite a passing 15b result.
